window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>For fans of moody and escapist psychological thrillers such as Patricia Highsmith’s <i>The Talented Mr. Ripley</i> or the new Audible Original <i>The Chateau</i>, this is your next suspenseful listen.</p> <p>Step into the hauntingly beautiful world of <i>Resort</i> by Oli Isaac–a fractured and surreal drama that blurs the lines between reality and illusion.</p> <p>Clara, a mystery shopper scraping by in London, is a compulsive chameleon, more comfortable playing a role than she is in her own skin. A once-in-a-career opportunity to review a luxury resort pairs her with a faux fiancé—Avery—and introduces her to a rarefied world of wealth and reinvention. Amid seductive opulence and the shadows of past lies, Clara faces a chilling question: Can you ever truly escape yourself?</p> <p>Starring Phia Saban (<i>House of the Dragon</i>), Daryl McCormack (<i>Peaky Blinders, Bad Sisters</i>), and Charlotte Ritchie (<i>You</i>), <i> Resort</i> is a slow-burn, mesmerizing audio experience across twelve chapters. Directed by Julia Head with sound design by Mikhail Fiksel, the team behind <i>Massive</i>.</p> <p>Playwright Oli Isaac was awarded a commission through the Audible Emerging Playwrights Fund, an initiative dedicated to developing innovative original plays driven by language and voice. As an Audible-commissioned playwright, they received funding and creative support to develop <i>Resort</i>.</p>"; 
